Mouse infertility (Ccnyl1). Spermiogenesis defects, but normal counts (https://journals.plos.org/plosgenetics/article?id=10.1371/journal.pgen.1005485)
Human and mouse infertility. Sperm motility defects (https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3283211/ and http://www.informatics.jax.org/marker/phenotypes/MGI:2384917)
Mouse infertility 1/3 (Clgn). Defective sperm migration and interaction with the egg (http://www.jbc.org/content/286/7/5639.full)
Mouse infertility (for Ezh1 + Ezh2). Spermatogonia and meiotic defects (https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5389884/)
Mouse infertility (for Ezh1 + Ezh2). Spermatogonia and meiotic defects (https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5389884/)
Mouse infertility. Early germ cell defects (https://academic.oup.com/hmg/article/11/24/3047/653267)
Mouse infertility 1/2 (for Fgfr3). No detailed phenotype (https://www.jax.org/strain/014182)
Mouse infertility 2/2 (for Khdrbs1). Meiotic and  spermiogenesis defects (http://jcb.rupress.org/content/185/2/235)
Mouse infertility 1/2 (for Kif18a). Cell cycle defects (https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2963078/)
Mouse infertility (Lpin1). Possibly due to behavior impairment (http://www.jbc.org/content/266/18/11955.full.pdf)
Mouse infertility 1/2 (Man2a2). Defective adhesion between somatic and germ cells (https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/12417422)

Mouse infertility 2/3 (for either Piwil1 or Piwil2). Meiotic (Piwil2) or spermiogenesis (Piwil1) defects (https://dev.biologists.org/content/131/4/839.long and https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S153458070200165X?via%3Dihub)

Mouse infertility 1/3 (for either Piwil1 or Piwil2). Meiotic (Piwil2) or spermiogenesis (Piwil1) defects (https://dev.biologists.org/content/131/4/839.long and https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S153458070200165X?via%3Dihub)
Mouse infertility. Sperm motility defects and slight reduction in number (https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3733543/)
Mouse infertility 1/3 (for Prkaca). Slight reduction of sperm counts and motility defects (https://academic.oup.com/mend/article/16/3/630/2741756)
Mouse infertility (for Safb1). Spermatogenesis defects, with abnormal hormonal levels (https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC1069606/)
Mouse infertility (Sirt1). Meiotic defects, but germ cell-independent (https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/18987333)
Mouse infertility (Tdrd5). Meiotic and spermiogenesis defects (https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3051809/)
Mouse infertility. Meiotic and sperm tail defects (https://dev.biologists.org/content/25/2/223.long)
Mouse infertility 1/2 (for VDAC3). Sperm axoneme defects (https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/11507092)
Mouse infertility (for Wdr62). Defects in meiotic initiation (https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6107287/)
